    "causal_summary": "The three MCP launchers (`mk-skill-advisor-launcher.cjs`, `mk-code-index-launcher.cjs`, `mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs`) all shared the same architectural smell: nothing prevented multiple launcher instances from running concurrently in the same workspace. Skill-advisor's SQLite quarantine path turned that smell into a visible failure (1005 `.corrupt` files in 6 hours during a benchmark run). Code-graph and spec-memory absorbed the race silently because their WAL + busy_timeout settings happened to be compatible, but the same code-path could have failed under different conditions.",
